    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="01"/><w n="5">Τῆι</w> <w lemma="σύνοδος" rend="συνόδωι" n="10">συνόδωι</w> <w lemma="ὁ" rend="τῶν" n="15">τῶν</w> <w lemma="συγγεοῦχος" rend="συνγεούχων" n="20">συνγεούχων</w>
                    <lb n="02"/><w n="25">Πτολεμαῖος</w> <w n="30">Ἀλεξάνδρου</w>
                    <lb n="03"/><w n="35">Αἰακιδεύς.</w> <w n="40">(</w> <w rend="ἔτους" n="45">ἔτους</w>) <w n="50">κ.</w>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus"><!-- references in note will go in @source on app once bibliography is encoded -->
                   <p/>
            </div> 
            <div type="translation">
                <p>To the association of fellow landowners, Ptolemaios the son of Alexandros, of the deme Aiakideus, (dedicated this), year 20.</p>
            </div> 
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This dedicatory plaque for an association of landowners is offered by an Alexandrian citizen with the impeccably dynastic name of Ptolemy the son of Alexander. The date in line 3 is cut slightly out of vertical alignment; the lettering of the inscription belongs to the later second or first century, so that year 20 is more likely to belong to the reign of Ptolemy X (95-4) or XII (62-1) than Ptolemy VI (162-1).</p>
            </div>
